00:38:32.070 --> 00:38:33.370
&gt;&gt; Who were the trainers?

00:38:33.370 --> 00:38:37.050
All boxers, who trained
them for the boxing matches?

00:38:37.050 --> 00:38:42.870
Who trained these young
men to become boxers?

00:38:42.870 --> 00:38:49.220
&gt;&gt; The question is who
prepared-in other words,

00:38:49.220 --> 00:38:50.520
was there an organization?

00:38:50.520 --> 00:38:51.820
Was this organized?

00:38:51.820 --> 00:38:53.790
&gt;&gt; Was this organized
with the trainers or?

00:38:53.790 --> 00:38:56.740
&gt;&gt; Okay, boxing was
very unorganized.

00:38:56.740 --> 00:38:58.480
That's a very good question.

00:38:58.480 --> 00:39:08.030
In 1905, in 1906, there were 16
boxers who were killed in the ring.

00:39:08.030 --> 00:39:11.220
And I knew there were
problems in football,

00:39:11.220 --> 00:39:14.980
and a lot of the articles said
that boxing is not as rough,

00:39:14.980 --> 00:39:16.500
or more rough than football,

00:39:16.500 --> 00:39:21.030
and I wondered just how
rough football was in 1906.

00:39:21.030 --> 00:39:23.040
Looking it up, ironically,

00:39:23.040 --> 00:39:28.500
what I found was there were 16
football players in 1905 and 1906.

00:39:28.500 --> 00:39:30.940
I continued, and I
looked up horse racing,

00:39:30.940 --> 00:39:35.760
and I found out there were 16
jockeys who were killed in 1906,

00:39:35.760 --> 00:39:40.480
eight of them on a horse, the other
8 were killed in other incidents.

00:39:40.480 --> 00:39:47.940
So there was a lot of-there
was danger in all the sports,

00:39:47.940 --> 00:39:50.610
but football was organized,
to answer your question,

00:39:50.610 --> 00:39:54.340
and football addressed the
flying wedge in different forms

00:39:54.340 --> 00:39:57.220
of football, to lessen the danger.

00:39:57.220 --> 00:40:01.080
The way the deaths in
boxing were handled was

00:40:01.080 --> 00:40:04.240
that they would handle
it as a criminal matter.

00:40:04.240 --> 00:40:07.440
And Lewis, Harry Lewis, and I spent
a lot of time in the book on this,

00:40:07.440 --> 00:40:09.980
Harry Lewis actually
killed a man in the ring,

00:40:09.980 --> 00:40:12.810
and they charged him with murder.

00:40:12.810 --> 00:40:17.970
So that's-that's what boxing got,
because they weren't organized.

00:40:17.970 --> 00:40:21.140
You asked the question about
who arranged the matches.

00:40:21.140 --> 00:40:25.060
The matches were arranged by
whoever was the best negotiator.

00:40:25.060 --> 00:40:30.430
Each boxer had someone looking out
for them, somebody in the family,

00:40:30.430 --> 00:40:33.600
or he had no one looking out for
him, and looked out for himself.

00:40:33.600 --> 00:40:36.970
Most of those guys got
taken advantage of.

00:40:36.970 --> 00:40:40.610
But there was an awful lot
of skullduggery in boxing,

00:40:40.610 --> 00:40:42.700
probably was in football
and baseball too [laughs],

00:40:42.700 --> 00:40:46.180
I didn't write about them.

00:40:46.180 --> 00:40:48.830
But I don't know if that
quite answers your question,

00:40:48.830 --> 00:40:53.960
but I would say it was basically an
unorganized sport, and no one tried

00:40:53.960 --> 00:40:58.120
to organize it before 1915.

00:40:58.120 --> 00:41:07.230
By 1930s, when prohibition was
being phased out, and the mafia

00:41:07.230 --> 00:41:12.440
and different gangs felt there
was money to be made in boxing,

00:41:12.440 --> 00:41:17.880
then the criminal element
entered boxing in a big way,

00:41:17.880 --> 00:41:21.370
at the management and
promotional level.

