00:41:29.430 --> 00:41:31.180
&gt;&gt; At one point in this
century did Jewish involvement

00:41:31.180 --> 00:41:34.530
in boxing start to taper off?

00:41:34.530 --> 00:41:35.830
&gt;&gt; That's a good question.

00:41:35.830 --> 00:41:40.310
The question is at what point in
this century did Jewish boxing tend

00:41:40.310 --> 00:41:43.570
to taper off, and the
answer to that is,

00:41:43.570 --> 00:41:48.620
when Congress passed the quota
act in 1924, up until 1924,

00:41:48.620 --> 00:41:55.860
there was another quota act in
1921, but in 24, they cut off all,

00:41:55.860 --> 00:41:59.160
for practical purposes,
immigration from Russia.

00:41:59.160 --> 00:42:03.480
Almost all of the fighters
did it for money.

00:42:03.480 --> 00:42:06.440
Almost all of the fighters
were poor.

00:42:06.440 --> 00:42:10.390
And all of the fighters knew
that if their father had died,

00:42:10.390 --> 00:42:13.770
like Tendler's father, somebody had
to make the money for the family,

00:42:13.770 --> 00:42:16.360
and they could make a
lot more money fighting

00:42:16.360 --> 00:42:17.770
than they could being newsboys.

00:42:17.770 --> 00:42:21.160
He was a newsboy, and a
fighter, both at the same time.

00:42:21.160 --> 00:42:26.510
And so beginning in 1924,
there was no more immigration.

00:42:26.510 --> 00:42:30.730
So then the boys that were being
brought up, the Jewish boys,

00:42:30.730 --> 00:42:33.910
felt that gee, this boxing
thing is kind of rough,

00:42:33.910 --> 00:42:37.920
maybe I'm better off going to
college, or something like that,

00:42:37.920 --> 00:42:40.640
and becoming a lawyer,
becoming a doctor.

00:42:40.640 --> 00:42:45.310
If this is really an open country,
and we know there were restrictions

00:42:45.310 --> 00:42:47.770
at Harvard and different
ivy league schools,

00:42:47.770 --> 00:42:52.390
that it might still be a better
risk than getting in the ring

00:42:52.390 --> 00:42:54.990
and getting my brains knocked out.

00:42:54.990 --> 00:43:00.610
So it started to drop off
as far as new young boxers,

00:43:00.610 --> 00:43:05.020
I would say, in the early 1930s.

00:43:05.020 --> 00:43:09.730
But during the 1930s, they still
had full-grown Jewish boxers,

00:43:09.730 --> 00:43:11.650
in the 1920s.

00:43:11.650 --> 00:43:15.520
But if you went to a
training ring at that time,

00:43:15.520 --> 00:43:19.470 position:56%
there would be no young boys, six or
seven, looking up at their heroes.

00:43:19.470 --> 00:43:22.180
There would be none of those,
because there were no immigrants.

00:43:22.180 --> 00:43:28.400
In 1906, I think I mentioned,
there were 125,000 Jews from Russia

00:43:28.400 --> 00:43:30.140
who came to the United States.

00:43:30.140 --> 00:43:33.320
In 1933, there were 2,000.

00:43:33.320 --> 00:43:37.400
That is how effective the
quota act of 1924 was.

